&lt;p style="margin-bottom: 15px; font-style: italic;"&gt;According to a deeply alarming new report in The Atlantic by Sarah Fitzpatrick, FBI Director Kash Patel has spent his tenure as director bouncing between paranoia, erratic behavior, unexplained absences and what multiple sources described as excessive drinking. At one point, Patel reportedly became convinced he had been fired because he was briefly unable to log into an FBI computer system. He then began frantically calling aides and allies in a panic, even though he had not actually been fired at all.&lt;/p&gt;
